observations.recommendation:
We recommended and the Management agreed to facilitate the conduct of the one-time cleansing of PPE by performing the following:
Identify other departments within the LGU that may have available staff with relevant skills (e.g., record-keeping, accounting, or logistics) who can be temporarily reassigned to assist and focus with the inventory process;
Establish a new set of Inventory Committee, ensuring that the members of the Inventory committee attend relevant trainings on its conduct;
Ensure that the Inventory Committee will be temporarily relieved of their regular duties until the completion of the physical inventory within a clear and agreed-upon timeline;
Ensure that the Inventory Committee assign a unique Property Number for each PPE item following the required code format in the numbering system as provided in Section 5 of the Circular; and
Ensure that the newly reconstituted Inventory Committee prepare and submit the approved PIP to the COA Audit Team at least 10 calendar days before the scheduled start of the inventory-taking process.

We recommended and the Management agreed to:
Comply with COA Circular No. 97-002 when granting cash advances to ensure full compliance with established guidelines;
Discontinue the current practice of granting cash advance for unauthorized purposes and to ineligible officials, as it violates prescribed government disbursement procedures;
Require that only duly appointed or designated disbursing officers may perform disbursing functions; and
Ensure that all units of the LGU adopt public bidding in the procurement of goods and services and resort only to alternative modes of procurement in highly exceptional cases provided and allowed in the implementing rules and regulations of RA No. 9184.

We recommended and Management agreed to:
Comply with COA Circular No. 97-002 and Section 93 of PD No. 1445, which require that all government payments be made either by check, payable directly to the creditor or supplier or through cash advances granted only to authorized disbursing officers for specific, approved purposes;
Discontinue the current practice of reimbursing municipal officials or employees who made payments in cash, as it violates prescribed government disbursement procedures;
Require that only designated disbursing officers handle cash payments, and such payments must be made exclusively through properly approved cash advances;
Ensure that all units of the LGU adopt public bidding in the procurement of goods and services in accordance with the implementing rules and regulations of RA No. 9184; and
Ensure that the Municipal Accountant withhold and remit the corresponding creditable income tax and percentage tax or final VAT, as appropriate, on future payments of procured goods and services.

We recommended that;
a. The Municipal Treasurer send a written notice to the payees of status and existence of the stale checks;
b. For improperly reported stale checks, the Office of the Municipal Treasurer and the Office of the Municipal Accountant, provide evidence that the checks are not outstanding; that they have been voided and no obligations exist; and
c. The Municipal Accountant to make the necessary adjusting entries to restore the deleted stale checks in the BRS.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor;
a. Direct the Accountant to ensure that personnel in the Accounting Office particularly those involved in the daily recording of transactions in the books of accounts to turn over the receipts and the necessary disbursement records with all paid vouchers and documents evidencing the transactions to the Auditor within ten (10) days from the date of receipt of said documents pursuant to COA Circular No. 95-006 dated May 18, 1995; and
b. Instruct and ensure that the Municipal Accountant to submit immediately the transaction documents such as DVs, Payrolls, ORs, JEVs for adjustments, liquidations, etc. and their corresponding supporting documents, and henceforth, submit it within the reglementary period to ensure their timely evaluation and that deficiencies and/or other observations will be also immediately corrected and/or adjusted.
